shortDescription: We've established a forward operations base on {TGT_SYSTEM.Name}. We need a competent lance to watch it while our regular forces are on maneuver. You should expect intermittent enemy contact from probing attacks and skirmishers.
longDescription: It may or may not be that easy, Commander. We may be a bit behind the front lines, but a FOB is an attractive target for our prospective employer's enemies.

objectiveList.title: Escort friendly vehicles to Base Defenses
Hidden Objective: Destroy the Third Lance
objectiveList.description: Hidden Objective: Destroy the Third Lance

dialogueContent.words: Maybe this will be a quiet contract for once--
Scratch that, Commander. Orbital imagery is showing multiple incoming hostile contacts.
Buckle up, Commander. This is going to get exciting.
Excellent work, Commander. A bit more action than advertised, but that's why they pay us the big C-Bills.
Well, that didn't go as planned; {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Name} can blame their poor intel.
Our employer's combat vehicles have arrived and activated the turrets.
Warning commander, sensors are reading multiple contacts approaching from multiple vectors. Looks like the attacking force has brought reinforcements.
Be advised, some of the target buildings are sustaining damage. Your mission is to keep them standing.
Commander, a target building has been demolished. Ensure the integrity of the remaining buildings.
Only one building still standing, Commander. We're cutting it awfully close, here.
Mercenary Commander, we've received word of the assault on your position. Reinforcements are incoming, they are about halfway there. Maintain position and you will be relieved and reinforced shortly.
Commander, on this outing we have some additional support from our employer.
They have point defenses set up around the base, they are however offline.
We have a friendly convoy with engineers who are eager to get at those defenses, so they can bring them online.
Escort them safely to the generators and we can boost our defensive capability with those turrets activated. Good Luck!
